Project design notes live under design/. System Jansson and system libcurl are
build/runtime dependencies; no third-party
Jansson or libcurl implementation source or upstream header source is vendored.
`src/snj_jansson_abi.h` is a GPL-2.0-only first-party declaration shim for
minimal build roots that provide the Jansson runtime library without the
development header; it contains no third-party implementation code and is
inventoried by `make depscheck`. `make depclosurecheck` captures and validates
the current-host dynamic executable closure, and `make evidencebundle`/
`make evidencecheck` provide a machine-readable release-evidence record. A
release must separately archive the complete concrete executable, Jansson,
libcurl backend, terminal, and live-provider evidence for each shipped platform
as required by the qualification checks.
